  "text": "In addition to their role in alleviating osmotic stress, ectoines also serve as stabilizers of macromolecules and even entire cells [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The function-preserving and anti-inflammatory effects of ectoines fostered substantial interest in exploring them for a variety of practical biotechnological applications and potential medical uses [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] .",
